  "prompt": "I am having problems with my friend. She is awesome, but she recently got a boyfriend. I just miss the way we once were. She's all over him and her other best friend. What should I do?",
  "response": "Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Talk to her openly and honestly about how you're feeling. Let her know you miss spending time together.\n\n2. Try to schedule some one-on-one time with her, like coffee or lunch.\n\n3. Be understanding that relationships change when someone starts dating, but also express that you value your friendship.\n\n4. Don't be jealous or pushy - that might push her away.\n\n5. Stay supportive of her relationship while also maintaining your own connection.\n\n6. Consider expanding your own social circle or pursuing other friendships to help fill the gap.\n\n7. If she's truly important to you, be patient and give her time to balance her relationships.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further or explore any of these suggestions in more detail?",
